The paper deals with improving the Feng-Rao bound for minimum distance of dual codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of well-behaving pairs, which is a concept in cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents numerical experiments, which could fall under the category of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
